In line element.
It is without conveying any specific semantic meaning.
Apply CSS styles or JaveScript actions to a part of the text.
-->

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>Document</title>
  </head>
  <body>
    <h1>Basic usage of the span tag for styling:</h1>

    <p>
      This is an example of a
      <span style="color: red; font-size: 20px">red</span> word within a
      sentence.
    </p>

    <h1>
      Using span for
      <span style="font-weight: bold; color: yellow; background-color: black;"
        >JavaScript</span
      >
      Interaction
    </h1>
    <p>
      Click <span onclick="alert('Hello')">here</span> to display agreeting.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
